deficit = metric:synthetic_forecast_oracle
close_directional_accuracy = 0.500254 < 0.95
```

Forecast semantic breakdown on protected eval `[760,1088)`:

```text
aggregate_count = 27552
aggregate_ev_mae = 0.0312739
aggregate_ev_rmse = 0.0512565
aggregate_directional_accuracy = 0.677555

price_features_directional_accuracy = 0.435721750
close_only_directional_accuracy = 0.500254000
activity_features_directional_accuracy = 1.000000000
```

Important metric caveat:

```text
The old aggregate directional score mixed price features with activity features.
Activity signs are trivial under the current log1p-style target coordinates,
so aggregate directional accuracy was misleading.

The feature-aware gate correctly focuses on close direction for the price
signal.
```

## Edge-Return Projection Results

The edge projection is closer to the policy question:

```text
quote node = SYNUSD
base nodes = SYNALPHA,SYNBETA,SYNGAMMA
close feature index = 3

predicted edge return = predicted_close(base) - predicted_close(quote)
realized edge return  = realized_close(base) - realized_close(quote)
```

